$echorc 
 
 Usage : echorc [-template expid nymd nhms] [-rc rcfile] rcstring
 
 rcstring                    string in rcfile that value is to be echoed 
 
 -template expid nymd nhms  specify when var is expected to be a GRADS template
 -rc       rcfilename       rc file name (default: fvpsas.rc)
 -ncol     column_number    when reading table, allows getting given column (default: 1)
 
 Example (using rc file): echorc.x -template myexp 20040101 060000 -rc myfile.rc templatename 
  with myfile.rc containing the following line: 
       templatename: %s.myfile.something.%y4%m2%d2_%h2z.bin 
  the result of echorc.x would be:  myexp.myfile.something.20040101_06z.bin 
 
 Example (direct template fill): 
    echorc.x -template myexp 20040101 060000 -fill %s.myfile.something.%y4%m2%d2_%h2z.bin 